REMARKS:  Diagnostic horizons and features recognized in this pedon are:  Mollic epipedon - from the soil surface to 7 inches, mixed (Ap, Bk1 horizons);
Calcic horizon - from 6 to 61 inches (Bk1, Bk2, Bk3 horizons);
Particle-size control section - from 10 to 40 inches (Bk2, Bk3 horizons).
Soil interpretation records:  MT0174, MT0354, MT0696.
Windham soils have a frigid temperature regime and an ustic moisture regime.
